  "doc_id": "22202",
  "text": "EBNA 1 has been detected in B lymphocytes 1 to 2 days after infection by the anticomplement immunofluorescence test (1, 15), while cellular DNA synthesis begins about 40 h postinfection (1, 5, 11) and mitosis and cell division begin about 8 h later [CITATION_1] . The present report has examined the induction of EBNA 1, EBNA 2, and other EBV-specific nuclear proteins and their relationship to cellular DNA synthesis.",
